    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="623"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d623">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1143.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram. ]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 30, 7 p.m. An aide mémoire was handed to the Italian ambassador and
                    copies sent in notes to the British, French, and German ambassadors containing
                    the text of the note to the minister for foreign affairs from Mr. Dearing, in
                    pursuance of Department’s March 16.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
